Really? Govenors assign equipment to units? Me thinks the Air Force does this - a governor might lobby the Air Force (more likely the President) to make a decision one way or another (most likely to save jobs if the Air Force is planning a change that will reduce the unit's personnel complement, not because he wants the unit to operate a specific type of equipment or perform a specific mission - it's doubtful he'd even recognize an F-16 if he saw on) but assign equipment?
